text: ¬†@samundradangol¬† I think youtube's system detects the uploaded clips as the "original" source, since the actual stream source is still ongoing. When that happens, sometimes youtube automatically marks or flags the actual stream as an identical video so the streamer gets a strike or something. It's common etiquette within the clippers to post clips after the stream ends, that's why you see sometimes that a bunch of clips get uploaded only as soon as streams finish.
